    "However, both papers rely on an intracranial setup that requires invasive brain surgery and is therefore not applicable to wearable surface EEG systems.",
    "Samiee et al.",
    "13 proposed a novel feature extraction technique called rational discrete short-time Fourier Transform.",
    "However, their work also bases the experiments on intracranial data, and despite achieving good sensitivity (97%), they have a false positive alarm rate of around 65 FP/h.",
    "In the study by Wang et al."
